      "side": 1,
      "message": "Looking at Maven Central, the Gemini SDK pulls in a massive transitive dependency tree (Jackson, OkHttp, Okio, and the Kotlin runtime): [1], which is overkill for a single provider call.\n\nTo keep the plugin lightweight and avoid potential classpath conflicts with Gerrit core, we can replace the SDK with a lean REST call using the Apache HttpClient already available in the Gerrit runtime:\n\nhttps://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models/%s:generateContent?key\u003d%s\n\nSimilar to how it was in the original version, as it was called from JS. This requires manual JSON parsing, though.",
